.
 The black hole seeds are allowed to grow through gas accretion or through
 mergers with other black holes.
 The black hole seeds are allowed to grow through gas accretion, parametrized
 in terms of Eddington limited Bondi-Hoyle-Lyttleton (BHL)-like accretion
 (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "bondi1952accretion,bondihoyle1044"

\end_inset

), or through mergers with other black holes.
 BHL is a non-spherical accretion flow which develops when a compact object
 moves relative to a uniform gas cloud.
 The BHL accretion rate on the black hole is given by
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\dot{M}_{B}=\frac{4\pi G^{2}M_{BH}^{2}\rho}{(c_{s}^{2}+v^{2})^{3/2}},
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $c_{s}$
\end_inset

 are the density and sound speed of the gas, respectively, 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 is a dimensionless parameter, and 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

 is the velocity of the black hole relative to the gas.
 
